  "texts": [
    "As highlighted in the figure, the first",
    "Matrix multiplication is equivalent of the dot product entry in row 1, column 1 is the dot product between row 1 from the Q matrix and column 1 from the transposed K matrix.",
    "To generalize, the scalar value in row i, column j of the S matrix is the dot product between row i of the Q matrix and column j of the K matrix.",
    "In general, the dot product of token vectors with themselves will tend to have the highest co-relevance scores, which are located along the diagonal of the S matrix.",
    "Non-identical token pairs with high co-relevance will have high scores that are located off the main diagonal."
  ],
